  "body": "Several days ago I submitted ~13k transactions to the node. All those transactions were sitting in the `queued` txpool section:\r\n\r\n```\r\n> txpool.status\r\n{\r\n  pending: 0,\r\n  queued: 12833\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nToday I changed the entrypoint script with txpool enhancements and now I have the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\n> txpool.status\r\n\r\n{\r\n  pending: 49285,\r\n  queued: 13277\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAll my transactions are transfer transactions to the same address and look like this one:\r\n\r\n```\r\n9999: \"0xe2Ee1ac57B2E5564522b2dE064A47b3f98B0e9c9: 0 wei + 100000 gas Ã— 2000000000 wei\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nNone of my transactions are in the `pending` section. Is it OK? Is there a way to make the promotion manually?\r\n\r\nHere's my geth startup command:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngeth --rpc --rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 \\\r\n--rpccorsdomain \"*\" \\\r\n--rpcport 6588 \\\r\n--rpcapi \"eth,net,web3,txpool\" \\\r\n--maxpeers \"125\" \\\r\n--cache \"8192\" \\\r\n --txpool.globalslots 4294967295 \\\r\n--txpool.accountqueue 429496729 \\\r\n--txpool.globalqueue 4294967295 \\\r\n--txpool.accountslots 429496729 \\\r\n--txpool.lifetime \"72h0m0s\" \\\r\n--trie-cache-gens \"1024\" \\\r\n--gasprice \"5000000000\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\n```\r\nGeth version:  Geth/v1.8.12-stable/linux-amd64/go1.10.3\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nBase image from the docker hub with custom entrypoint\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nTransactions should be pending, not queued\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAll my local transactions are queued, even though in the pedning list there're some transactions with lower gas price\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nI can provide `transactions.rlp` file with the queued transactions\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n",
